<font color="#FF0000">THE WALL</font><br>
<tt>Wed May 28 12:44:16 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I went to the Wall in the spring of 1987, the cherry blossoms, and the tourists were in full bloom.  I stood before the tallest section of the wall, overwhelmed by a flood of emotions that I could not sort out or understand.<br>
The whole experience came into focus when I heard a woman kneeling before the wall with a child, and while pointing to a name, she said, &quot;There's' your Daddy's name right there.&quot;   Semper Fi Carl.<br>

